Hanged out with a gym boomer friend who used to be a Vegas taxi driver in the Clinton era. He was friends with Mike Tyson, a few NBA guys, lots of anecdotes from him. They went to the same strip club with Tyson, he remembers him buying Rolex watches for anyone in his circles.

Most interesting thing he said is giving a ride to people who lost millions at a casino, who literally lost their entire wealth, he would give them a ride and see their names in the newspapers a few days later, offed themselves at a bridge or with a shotgun
